ent of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Teller%E2%80%93Ulam_design\" title=\"Teller\u2013Ulam design\" class=\"mw-redirect\">thermonuclear weapons<\/a>. Sakharov later became an advocate of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Civil_liberties\" title=\"Civil liberties\">civil liberties<\/a> and civil reforms in the Soviet Union, for which he faced state persecution; these efforts earned him the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Peace_Prize\" title=\"Nobel Peace Prize\">Nobel Peace Prize<\/a> in 1975. The <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Sakharov_Prize\" title=\"Sakharov Prize\">Sakharov Prize<\/a>, which is awarded annually by the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/European_Parliament\" title=\"European Parliament\">European Parliament<\/a> for people and organizations dedicated to human rights and freedoms, is named in his honour.<sup id=\"cite_ref-aip.org_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Andrei_Dmitrievich_Sakharov#cite_note-aip.org-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Andrei Dmitrievich Sakharov","place_of_birth":"Moscow ,  RSFSR","place_of_death":"Moscow ,  USSR","text":"Andrei Dmitrievich Sakharov , Peace, 1975","year":1975.0}